            "@type": "PropertyValue",
            "name": "reveries",
            "value": "1. She remembers the clatter of mahjong tiles and her mother\u2019s hushed Cantonese conversations with neighbors in their Richmond District apartment. It wasn't just the language, but the unspoken communication, the intricate network of support and gossip, that imprinted on her young mind a sense of community beneath the city's surface, shaping her understanding of how people connect.\n\n2. The smell of eucalyptus along the paths near Strawberry Creek in Berkeley, during late-night study sessions. The quiet hum of students, the shared exhaustion and camaraderie, solidified the knowledge that learning and growth were intertwined with connection, a feeling she carries into her collaborative approach at work.\n\n3. That nerve-wracking community meeting about the Muni line extension, the room thick with frustration. A resident, voice shaking, shared their daily commute struggles. In that moment, the plans on paper felt real, visceral, fueling her resolve to build not just infrastructure, but hope and access, solidifying her purpose.\n\n4. The feeling of the wind on her face cycling home over the hill into Bernal Heights after a particularly tough day. The relief, the sweeping view of the city lights, was a physical manifestation of finding her place \u2013 grounded yet expansive, a reminder of the beauty and resilience she fights for daily.\n\n5. Watching the sunset from Indian Rock Park with friends, a blur of laughter and shared dreams for the city. It wasn't about one specific conversation, but the collective energy, the feeling of being understood and supported, a cornerstone of her emotional landscape that sustains her demanding work."
